The paper deals with non-malleable codes, which are a cryptographic concept, and their application to transmission over Arbitrary Varying Channels (AVCs), which are a communication theory concept. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the protection against tampering, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper uses binary (discrete memoryless) AVCs, which is a subfield of communication theory, and hence cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the encoding scheme, which involves the use of algorithms, and hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the transmission of messages over channels, which is a subfield of networking, and hence cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category.
